SaLT: Service and Learning Together

Inspiring Young People to Change Their World

SaLT's Guiding Principles

Respect | Communicate Love | This Is It | Be Flexible | Unplug | Little By Little | Bring It Home

SaLT is:

  • Service to meet the needs of a community
  • Learning about the world and oneself
  • Together creating long-lasting relationships

SaLT Values:

  • Engaging in meaningful service
  • Expanding personal knowledge and growth
  • Challenging current understandings
  • Working for a common purpose
  • Creating deep friendships

Join SaLT and...

  • Learn Empathy
  • Reflect and Grow
  • Leave Your Comfort Zone
  • Meet New People/Cultures
  • Have Fun Making a Difference!

Service-Learning Trips & Service Projects

Service Projects: Shop N' Drop & Love2Learn

Service-Learning Trips: SaLT in ORLANDO, SaLT in NOLA, SaLT in Puerto Rico & SaLT in ALASKA

Our Mission:

To create meaningful service-learning experiences that meet the needs of the local community while promoting personal growth and understanding.
